    },
    {
      "id": "sybil_2_listing_2",
      "firm_id": "sybil_2",
      "description": "This 1994 Mazda RX-7 FD is a mechanically sound example of the legendary 13B-REW sequential twin-turbocharged rotary. The engine pulls strongly through the entire power band, with the transition between the primary and secondary turbos remaining seamless. It features the original five-speed manual transmission and a Torsen limited-slip differential, ensuring the 50/50 weight distribution is fully exploited through the corners. To address common platform heat-soak issues, this FD has been fitted with an upgraded aluminum radiator and silicone vacuum lines. The double-wishbone suspension remains tight, providing the tactile steering feedback these cars are famous for. A well-sorted enthusiast's car ready for the canyon roads.",
      "price": 34500.0,
      "reputation": 0.5,
      "quality": "poor",
      "quality_value": 0.1,
      "timestep_posted": 47
    },
    {
